---

<Legal
  title="Cookie Policy | MLogTech"
  description="What this website stores in your browser, and why. Spoiler: very little."
  h1="Cookie Policy."
  updated="July 17, 2026 (draft)"
>
  <h2>1. The short version</h2>
  <p>
    This website currently sets no advertising or analytics cookies. It stores one preference in
    your browser and nothing else.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What we store</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Duration</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>theme</td>
        <td>localStorage (not a cookie)</td>
        <td>Remembers your light/dark mode choice</td>
        <td>Until you clear it</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>3. Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    If we adopt a web analytics tool, it will be privacy-respecting, this table will be updated,
    and where consent is required a consent banner will be shown before anything non-essential is
    set.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-party embeds</h2>
  <p>
    Demo videos on this site are loaded from YouTube only after you press play. Until then, no
    YouTube code runs on the page. When you play a video, YouTube's own cookie practices apply.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Managing storage</h2>
  <p>
    You can clear the stored preference at any time through your browser's site data settings. The
    site keeps working; it just forgets your theme choice.
  </p>
</Legal>
